<subSubSection id="0CF865053259FF91FF1CFC10FCD6E058" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="445D368E3259FF91FF1CFC10FCD6E058" blockId="17.[151,1437,1662,2013]" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C3259FF91FF1CFC10FE92E1E9" bold="true" box="[151,326,1662,1689]" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">Type material.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="9B59882C3259FF91FEC5FC10FE62E1E8" box="[334,438,1663,1689]" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">Holotype</typeStatus>
(male). “Surabad / Typus / Turkestan 189 / 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D3259FF91FC27FC10FAC5E1E8" authority="F. Mor." authorityName="F. Mor." box="[940,1297,1663,1689]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguliventre">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C3259FF91FC27FC10FB61E1E8" box="[940,1205,1663,1689]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">Anthidium anguliventre</emphasis>
F. Mor.
</taxonomicName>
/ http://coll. mfn-berlin.de/u” (
<collectionCode id="22F3AE4B3259FF91FEEEFCCCFE73E1CC" box="[357,423,1699,1725]" country="Germany" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/8syf-d21i" name="Museum für Naturkunde Berlin (Zoological Collections)" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" type="Museum">ZMB</collectionCode>
). Note: Surabad is not located in 
<collectingCountry id="3CF5761E3259FF91FCB8FCCCFC1AE1CC" box="[819,974,1699,1725]" name="Turkmenistan" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">Turkmenistan</collectingCountry>
as indicated on the label and by 
<bibRefCitation id="20734B7F3259FF91FAD3FCCCFF30E190" author="Friese, H." pageId="17" pageNumber="499" refId="ref17078" refString="Friese, H. (1898) Die Bienen Europa ' s (Apidae europaeae) nach ihren Gattungen, Arten und Varietaten auf vergleichend morphologisch-biologischer Grundlage. Theil IV. Solitare Apiden: Genus Eriades. Genus Trachusa. Genus Anthidium. R. Friedla ¨ nder, Berlin, 303 pp." type="book" year="1898">Friese (1898)</bibRefCitation>
, but in 
<collectingCountry id="3CF5761E3259FF91FEBDFCA8FEB7E190" box="[310,355,1735,1761]" name="Iran" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">Iran</collectingCountry>
as found out by 
<bibRefCitation id="20734B7F3259FF91FD96FCA8FD65E190" author="Baker, D. B." box="[541,689,1735,1761]" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" pagination="823 - 860" refId="ref16669" refString="Baker, D. B. (1998) Taxonomic and phylogenetic problems in Old World eucerine bees, with special reference to the genus Tarsalia Morawitz, 1895 (Hymenoptera: Apoidea: Anthophoridae). Journal of Natural History, 32, 823 - 860. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222939800770441" type="journal article" year="1998">Baker (1998)</bibRefCitation>
based on the travel itinerary of the collector, D. K. Glasonov [Glazunov]. Coordinates: 35° 
<geoCoordinate id="21D650493259FF91FE24FC85FE39E074" box="[431,493,1770,1797]" degrees="43" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" precision="55555" value="43.0">43°N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="21D650493259FF91FE73FC85FD8CE074" box="[504,600,1770,1797]" degrees="61" direction="east" minutes="05" orientation="longitude" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" precision="925" value="61.083332">61°05’E</geoCoordinate>
. Genitalia are dissected (by F. Friese?) and available, but their preservation status does not allow examination of the relevant traits.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0CF865053259FF91FF4CFD5DFE3CE0C8" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="445D368E3259FF91FF4CFD5DFE3CE0C8" blockId="17.[151,1437,1662,2013]" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C3259FF91FF4CFD5DFE96E03D" bold="true" box="[199,322,1842,1868]" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The most similar species is 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D3259FF91FDF6FD5CFCDCE03C" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1980" box="[637,776,1843,1869]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundum">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C3259FF91FDF6FD5CFCDCE03C" box="[637,776,1843,1869]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">A. rotundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with which the male shares particularly the median furrow on S6. However, it is distinguished from that species and all other members of the subgenus by a strong lamella on the preoccipital ridge. Punctation on tergal discs more scattered than in 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D3259FF91FC4FFD14FB84E0E4" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1980" box="[964,1104,1915,1941]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundum">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C3259FF91FC4FFD14FB84E0E4" box="[964,1104,1915,1941]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">A. rotundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. T2 laterally rounded (lateral tooth present in 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D3259FF91FEC7FDF0FE03E0C8" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1980" box="[332,471,1951,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundum">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C3259FF91FEC7FDF0FE03E0C8" box="[332,471,1951,1977]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">A. rotundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0CF865053259FF92FF4CFDADFDCEE137" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="500" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" type="description">
<paragraph id="445D368E3259FF92FF4CFDADFBD5E511" blockId="17.[151,1437,1662,2013]" lastBlockId="18.[151,1437,150,609]" lastPageId="18" lastPageNumber="500" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C3259FF91FF4CFDADFE70E0AC" bold="true" box="[199,420,1986,2013]" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">Description. Male.</emphasis>
<quantity id="831A9B6B3259FF91FE20FDACFE29E0AC" box="[427,509,1987,2013]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="17" pageNumber="499" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
. 
<emphasis id="7696EA9C3259FF91FD83FDACFD91E0AC" box="[520,581,1987,2013]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="499">Head</emphasis>
: Clypeus flat, anterior margin straight, posterior margin shallowly emarginate; apical margin brown, smooth; median third of clypeus almost impunctate; mandible yellow with three strong teeth; supraclypeal and lower paraocular area yellow, upper paraocular area with yellow band along inner orbit of eye and confluent with yellow maculation on vertex; vertex with broad ochreous to yellow transverse band, confluent with yellow gena; strong lamella (approx. 
<quantity id="831A9B6B325AFF92FD62FB6DFC9AE66C" box="[745,846,258,285]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" unit="mm" value="0.13">0.13 mm</quantity>
high) extending to height of middle of eye; antenna ochreous; underside of scape yellow.— 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FDDAFB48FCFAE631" authority=": Scutum" authorityName="Scutum" box="[593,814,294,321]" class="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" family="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" genus="Mesosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Crustacea (awaiting allocation)" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FDDAFB48FD1DE631" box="[593,713,295,320]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Mesosoma</emphasis>
: Scutum
</taxonomicName>
black, densely punctated; broad L-shaped anterolateral yellow band; remnants of a thin yellow longitudinal line next to the middle; scutellum and axillae yellow, scutellum with some black colouration anteriorly and with median emargination; axilla slightly protruding laterally; propodeal triangle rugulose, coarser at base than apically; upper half of mesepisternum yellow, lower half black; pronotal lobe lamellate.— 
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FED2FBD8FE1AE6A1" box="[345,462,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Metasoma</emphasis>
: Tergal discs punctate, with distance between punctures up to 1–2 puncture diameter; depressions T1–T6 chestnut-brown; T3–T6 each with a lateral tooth, small in T3 and becoming larger towards T6; teeth flat with transparent lamella-like margin; disc of T6 bulging on each side of the middle; T7 semicircular with transparent margin (
<figureCitation id="DCD92A0B325AFF92FEFCF84DFE07E54D" box="[375,467,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURE 8" captionStartId="11.[151,250,945,969]" captionTargetBox="[158,1429,181,920]" captionTargetId="figure-39@11.[158,1429,181,921]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 8. Apical terga of the male of five species of Anthidium, subgenus Gulanthidium: A. Anthidium anguliventre; B. A. eremicum; C. A. occidentale sp. nov.; D. A. preoccipitale sp. nov.; E. A. rotundum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531651" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531651/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Figs 8D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="DCD92A0B325AFF92FE55F84DFDD6E54D" box="[478,514,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1689,1713]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,1036,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-81@11.[162,1425,1029,1665]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male of Anthidium, subgenus Gulanthidium. Apical terga (upper row) in dorsal and sternum 6 (S6) in ventral view. A + D. Anthidium anguliventre; B + E. A. eremicum and A. occidentale; C + F. A. preoccipitale and A. rotundum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531653/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">9C</figureCitation>
); S6 semicircular with median furrow and lateral depression (
<figureCitation id="DCD92A0B325AFF92FB25F84DFAD4E54D" box="[1198,1280,546,572]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="11.[151,250,1689,1713]" captionTargetBox="[168,1418,1036,1652]" captionTargetId="figure-81@11.[162,1425,1029,1665]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURE 9. Male of Anthidium, subgenus Gulanthidium. Apical terga (upper row) in dorsal and sternum 6 (S6) in ventral view. A + D. Anthidium anguliventre; B + E. A. eremicum and A. occidentale; C + F. A. preoccipitale and A. rotundum." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531653" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531653/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Fig. 9F</figureCitation>
).— 
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FAA0F84CFAB4E54D" box="[1323,1376,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Legs</emphasis>
: Yellow, inner faces black or dark brown; hind basitarsus with longitudinal carina.
</paragraph>
<caption id="109D6606325AFF92FF1CFE86FC3CE254" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531663" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5531663" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531663/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" startId="18.[151,250,1257,1281]" targetBox="[189,1398,632,1234]" targetPageId="18">
<paragraph id="445D368E325AFF92FF1CFE86FC3CE254" blockId="18.[151,1436,1257,1318]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FF1CFE86FEF4E270" bold="true" box="[151,288,1257,1281]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">FIGURE 14.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FEADFE85FDCFE273" authority="Kasparek, 2021" authorityName="Kasparek" authorityYear="2021" box="[294,539,1258,1282]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preoccipitale" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FEADFE85FDCFE273" box="[294,539,1258,1282]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Anthidium preoccipitale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FDAAFE85FDA5E273" bold="true" box="[545,625,1258,1282]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="6DA557E7325AFF92FDAAFE85FDA5E273" box="[545,625,1258,1282]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Head in frontal and lateral view. Note the lamella on the high preoccipital ridge 
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FF1CFF62FF6FE254" bold="true" box="[151,187,1293,1317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">(A)</emphasis>
and the upwards projecting vertex with a sharply angular preoccipital ridge 
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FC4BFF62FC36E254" bold="true" box="[960,994,1293,1317]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">(B)</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="445D368E325AFF92FF4CFF3BFDCEE137" blockId="18.[151,1437,1364,2038]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FF4CFF3BFEA5E21F" bold="true" box="[199,369,1364,1390]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Morphometry</emphasis>
. Some measurements of the male 
<typeStatus id="9B59882C325AFF92FC8FFF3BFCB2E21F" box="[772,870,1364,1390]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FC19FF3BFB93E21F" authorityName="Kasparek" authorityYear="2021" box="[914,1095,1364,1390]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preoccipitale">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FC19FF3BFB93E21F" box="[914,1095,1364,1390]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. preoccipitale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were compared with a series (N=14) of males 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FEDDFF17FE35E2E3" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1980" box="[342,481,1400,1426]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundum">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FEDDFF17FE35E2E3" box="[342,481,1400,1426]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. rotundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(see under “material examined” there): the ocellocular distance, the hind ocellus-vertex distance, the distance between the posterior ocelli, and the distance between anterior and posterior ocelli. None of these measurements alone was strong enough to distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FCE0FFAFFBCBE2AB" authorityName="Kasparek" authorityYear="2021" box="[875,1055,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preoccipitale">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FCE0FFAFFBCBE2AB" box="[875,1055,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. preoccipitale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FBECFFAFFB21E2AB" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1980" box="[1127,1269,1472,1498]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundum">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FBECFFAFFB21E2AB" box="[1127,1269,1472,1498]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. rotundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, the combination of these five parameters showed in a Discriminant Function Analysis (DFA) that the discriminant score of 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FF3DFC67FEBCE153" authorityName="Kasparek" authorityYear="2021" box="[182,360,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preoccipitale">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FF3DFC67FEBCE153" box="[182,360,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. preoccipitale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is higher than in 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FDA0FC67FD63E153" authorityName="Warncke" authorityYear="1980" box="[555,695,1544,1570]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rotundum">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FDA0FC67FD63E153" box="[555,695,1544,1570]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. rotundum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="DCD92A0B325AFF92FD4DFC67FCCCE152" box="[710,792,1544,1571]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="19.[151,250,853,877]" captionTargetBox="[160,1428,188,822]" captionTargetId="figure-39@19.[151,1436,181,829]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 15. Comparison of some morphometric parameters regarding the distance of the ocelli from the eye and the preoccipital ridge (four parameters) between male Anthidium rotundum (grey) (N=14) and A. preoccipitale sp. nov. (scarlet) (N=1), based on a Discriminant Function Analysis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531665" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531665/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
), and this may be understood as further indication for the distinctiveness of 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FEEAFC43FDC7E137" authorityName="Kasparek" authorityYear="2021" box="[353,531,1580,1606]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preoccipitale">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FEEAFC43FDC7E137" box="[353,531,1580,1606]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. preoccipitale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0CF86505325AFF92FF4CFC20FB1AE11B" box="[199,1230,1615,1642]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="445D368E325AFF92FF4CFC20FB1AE11B" blockId="18.[151,1437,1364,2038]" box="[199,1230,1615,1642]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FF4CFC20FE70E118" bold="true" box="[199,420,1615,1641]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Derivatio nominis.</emphasis>
The name refers to the preoccipital ridge which bears a distinct lamella.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0CF86505325AFF92FF4CFC1CFE70E1FF" box="[199,420,1651,1678]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="445D368E325AFF92FF4CFC1CFE70E1FF" blockId="18.[151,1437,1364,2038]" box="[199,420,1651,1678]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FF4CFC1CFEF3E1FC" bold="true" box="[199,295,1651,1677]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Biology.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0CF86505325AFF92FF4CFCF8FB7EE1C3" box="[199,1194,1687,1714]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="445D368E325AFF92FF4CFCF8FB7EE1C3" blockId="18.[151,1437,1364,2038]" box="[199,1194,1687,1714]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FF4CFCF8FEB5E1C0" bold="true" box="[199,353,1687,1713]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Distribution.</emphasis>
Only known from the 
<typeStatus id="9B59882C325AFF92FDEBFCF7FD44E1C3" box="[608,656,1688,1714]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">type</typeStatus>
locality, situated in north-eastern 
<collectingCountry id="3CF5761E325AFF92FB86FCF7FBEEE1C3" box="[1037,1082,1688,1714]" name="Iran" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Iran</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="DCD92A0B325AFF92FBC1FCF7FB49E1C3" box="[1098,1181,1688,1714]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1739,1763]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,1073,1715]" captionTargetId="figure-52@14.[151,1435,1073,1715]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 12. Distribution of A. eremicum, A. flavissimum sp. nov., A. occidentale sp. nov., and A. preoccipitale sp. nov." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5531659" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5531659/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0CF86505325AFF92FF4CFCD3FE2CE087" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="445D368E325AFF92FF4CFCD3FE2CE087" blockId="18.[151,1437,1364,2038]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FF4CFCD3FEEFE1A7" bold="true" box="[199,315,1724,1750]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Remarks.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="9B59882C325AFF92FEFDFCD3FE0CE1A7" box="[374,472,1724,1750]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FE75FCD3FD65E1A7" authorityName="Kasparek" authorityYear="2021" box="[510,689,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preoccipitale">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FE75FCD3FD65E1A7" box="[510,689,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. preoccipitale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
male was provided to H. Friese together with a female 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FAA3FCD3FA49E1A7" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1804" box="[1320,1437,1724,1750]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FAA3FCD3FA49E1A7" box="[1320,1437,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">Anthidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the same location, and both specimens were regarded by him as 
<typeStatus id="9B59882C325AFF92FC39FC8FFBC9E18B" box="[946,1053,1760,1786]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">paratypes</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FBCFFC8FFB25E18B" box="[1092,1265,1760,1786]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguliventre">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FBCFFC8FFB25E18B" box="[1092,1265,1760,1786]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. anguliventre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As the collection date and other details are not available, it cannot be said whether these 
<specimenCount id="52E4FD07325AFF92FC67FD6BFB46E06F" box="[1004,1170,1796,1822]" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
were actually collected together. The identity of the female as 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FDC5FD47FD2EE033" box="[590,762,1832,1858]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguliventre">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FDC5FD47FD2EE033" box="[590,762,1832,1858]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. anguliventre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was confirmed here by a flat clypeus with a medially wide impunctate middle area, the punctation of T5 reaching the posterior margin, the laterally rounded T1–T2, and the presence of blunt teeth on T3–T5. In a Discriminant Function Analysis of six morphometric parameters of the clypeus, the female specimen also clearly clustered with 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FD67FDFBFC4CE0DF" box="[748,920,1940,1966]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguliventre">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FD67FDFBFC4CE0DF" box="[748,920,1940,1966]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. anguliventre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, it cannot be ruled out that this female is the unknown female of 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FD9EFDD7FD1CE0A3" authorityName="Kasparek" authorityYear="2021" box="[533,712,1976,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="preoccipitale">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FD9EFDD7FD1CE0A3" box="[533,712,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. preoccipitale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
which would then be indistinguishable from 
<taxonomicName id="83E24D0D325AFF92FB40FDD7FAACE0A3" box="[1227,1400,1976,2002]" class="Insecta" family="Megachilidae" genus="Anthidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="500" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anguliventre">
<emphasis id="7696EA9C325AFF92FB40FDD7FAACE0A3" box="[1227,1400,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="500">A. anguliventre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of external characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
